settings.title: Unsure which product  is right for you?
settings.text: Searching through the endless options can be confusing. Let us recommend the best product for your need.

settings.tab_content:
Compression supports contour to the shape of the affected area to provide even compression to reduce swelling and support for injured muscles and joints.

Best for: Within the first 72 hours of an acute (sudden) injury to reduce swelling & general support for ongoing muscle maintenance post injury.

For enhanced recovery and rehabilitation, our exclusive thermo regulation material has been clinically validated to convert moisture into heat working to increase muscle temperature and blood flow to aid recovery.

Best for: Post 72 hours & for chronic or overuse injuries for enhanced recovery and rehabilitation.

Designed with a unique 3 layer material technology to assist with performance, durability and comfort, during periods of increased activity.

Best for: Providing support during increased activity.

After meeting strict criteria, the Thermoskin range of heat retainer products have been endorsed – the first and only such range to carry the APA name. We are excited to put our name to such an excellent range of products.

settings.question: How should I wash my Thermoskin products?
settings.text:
It is recommended to place the product in a delicates washing bag. Machine wash in cold water.
Drip dry. Do not wring, twist, tumble dry, bleach or dry in direct sunlight. Do not wash in hot water
as this may cause the product to shrink in size.

settings.question: How often do you wash a Thermoskin thermal support or elastic?
settings.text:
If worn, around the house, at the office or in bed, wash Thermoskin every 2 or 3 days. If worn
during sports activity or heavy work, wash daily.

settings.question: How do I clean my elbow brace?
settings.text:
Supports can be washed inside a delicates bag in the machine, cold wash or hand washed. Do not
wring out or twist. Do not dry in direct sunlight or tumble dry.

settings.question: How long do you wear a thermal support for?
settings.text:
Thermoskin thermal supports can be worn at any time. For best results we recommend the
following:

  • During the winter months Thermoskin thermal supports can be worn prior to, during or
    after the activity. During the summer months Thermoskin should be worn before and after
    the activity only.
  • Use during the activity should be at the users discretion and comfort.

settings.question: Can you wear a thermal support to bed at night?
settings.text:
Yes, they can be worn to bed at night. Anecdotal evidence has shown that if the Thermoskin
thermal support is worn during sleep there is a minimising of pain occurring.

settings.question: What is the correct fit - Tight or Loose?
settings.text:
It is important that the correct size is worn to ensure effective treatment. To determine the size
required, use a tape measure and check the Thermoskin Measurement Chart to help with
selecting the correct size. Thermoskin products should be a comfortable fit, not too tight. These
size guides can be found on under each product listing or product box.

settings.question: Can you use it in conjunction with analgesic balms?
settings.text:
No, do not use ointments, liniments or oils under Thermoskin products as it reduces the life of the
product by breaking down the material. Creams and lotions when used under a Thermoskin
product could also irritate the skin.

settings.question: Do you always wear thermal supports against the skin?
settings.text: Yes, it should always be worn against the skin.

settings.question: What do you do if it causes skin irritation?
settings.text:
If a rash appears, discontinue use until the rash subsides. Wash the product and re-apply
periodically. To discourage the rash reappearing we recommend to users, that while bathing they
scrub the area that the product has covered. If a rash continues, please consult your Doctor.

settings.question: When is the best time to wear it?
settings.text:
For thermal treatment to be truly effective, the heat needs to be applied continuously for long
periods and during a range of activity levels. This is obviously impossible with traditional thermal
treatment that require immobility. Thermoskin thermal supports are an easier and convenient
form of thermal treatment.

settings.question: What is the difference between the Knee and the Knee Patella thermal supports?
settings.text: The Standard Knee is suitable for most applications, including patients with fluid retention around the kneecap. The Knee Patella allows more flexibility around the kneecap. As the kneecap is free from any compression, any tenderness or bruising that may be present on the kneecap itself will not be aggravated.

settings.question: Do Thermoskin Thermal Supports contain Latex?
settings.text: No. Thermoskin Thermal Supports are manufactured using 3 types of materials: nylon (outer layer), a non porous rubberised material (mid layer) and a synthetic fibre (Trioxon inner layer). None of these materials contain latex.

settings.question: Does Thermoskin offer custom made supports and braces?
settings.text: Yes, Thermoskin are proud to be the only business in Australia offering custom made supports and braces. Download the Thermoskin custom made order form or call 180 188 019 for more information.

settings.question: What is the warranty for these products?
settings.text: Thermoskin product warranty covers manufacturing faults for twelve months from the date of purchase. Does not cover misuse or wear and tear or change of mind.
